Everyone of us is imprisoned behind these four walls, sometimes by society and most of the time by us. But there is always a chance in life to throw off the chains and set ourselves free.⁣
⁣
Jaipur Rugs has provided both convicts and rural craftspeople with this freeing opportunity. What originally was a vision of embracing the traditional art form of weaving has now evolved into a number of initiatives that also aim to free a section of society imprisoned within the actual and fictitious boundaries constructed by society, thus crafting a better world one rug at a time!⁣
⁣
⁣

BRAHMAAND 
मनचाहा | MANCHAHA
ARTISANS OF JAIPUR RUGS X ASHIESH SHAH
The Manchaha rugs for Brahmaand are inspired by conversations between two designers: Ashiesh Shah and the weavers. Ideas, myths, and folklore about the solar system, celestial bodies far beyond, and the unperceivable universe are translated into intricate symbols and motifs paired with fine craftsmanship.
A unique design initiative by Jaipur Rugs that started off as a social experiment, the Manchaha rugs feature designs conceptualized by the weavers themselves with motifs and patterns inspired from their surroundings and daily lives.

With our new store in Bengaluru, we are taking the best of Jaipur to the heart of the Garden City. In the design of our new space, architect Khosla Associates have carved the pink city of Jaipur with a dynamic and sensual fluted wall that gently demarcates work areas from the display space. The wall motifs are inspired from the forts, palaces, and stepwells of the old city. Feature walls and ledges are handcrafted in local Banswara white marble from Rajasthan and the muted white stucco walls and ceilings form an understated backdrop for the rugs on display.⁣

latestPosts.caption:
Introducing the Atelier Collection by Vimar 1991 x Jaipur Rugs - the first collection of carpets created in collaboration with the Chanel-owned atelier of prestigious yarns.

Spun in Italy, woven in India, these rugs marry couture craftsmanship with timeless design. A signature monochrome palette, couture-inspired textures, and tailored geometrics echo the precision of fashion translated into texture-rich rugs and dhurries by master artisans across rural Rajasthan.

Photographed inside Deeppura Garh, the heritage home of Italian designer Maria Grazia Baldan, the carpets sit in quiet dialogue with the aarish-plastered borders and arched symmetry of traditional Rajasthani architecture, uniting two worlds in one space.

Location - @deeppuragarh 
Photo - @nevillesukhia

Jaipur Rugs x Kartik Research | Paris Fashion Week SS25

Jaipur Rugs was proud to create the catwalk for @kartikresearch debut on the Paris Fashion Week calendar, a bold call for the world to look to India not just for inspiration, but as the source. For the first time ever, Jaipur Rugs were used as a runway, with 24 handcrafted pieces layered with a touch of bohemia, grounding the show in stories of community, tradition, and craft.

Many congratulations to Kartik Kumra as the latest Indian designer to go global.
